<p>I've tried enabling the hyperlink in XML to no avail. <code>android:linksClickable="true"</code> doesn't seem to work for a lot of people, including me. The only thing that works is:</p>  <pre><code>TextView myTextView = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.myTextView); myTextView.setMovementMethod(LinkMovementMethod.getInstance()); </code></pre>  <p>The problem with this is that if you don't open the browser via the chooser (tap outside or back button), the link stays highlighted and it looks bad. When you tap the link again, it usually brings up the chooser again, but sometimes, it just deselects the link and you have to tap the link yet another time to bring back the chooser. This is pretty glitchy behavior for such a simple task. If the simple XML property worked as intended, that would be the simplest and easiest solution, but any solution is better than nothing.</p>  <p>Also, I tried the following code to deselect the link. The method is called, according to the log, but the link stays selected/highlighted.</p>  <pre><code>@Override protected void onResume() {     super.onResume();     TextView myTextView = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.myTextView);     myTextView.clearFocus();     myTextView.setSelected(false);     myTextView.setFocusable(false);     myTextView.setLinksClickable(false);     Log.d("test", "test"); } </code></pre>  <p><strong>XML for the TextView</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;TextView     android:layout_width="wrap_content"     android:layout_height="wrap_content"     android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"     android:text="@string/myTextView"     android:id="@+id/myTextView"     android:layout_alignParentTop="true"     android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"     android:layout_alignParentStart="true"     android:layout_alignParentRight="true"     android:layout_alignParentEnd="true" /&gt; </code></pre>